This is a brilliant plugin. Very useful and pretty easy to use.  Love the telemetry feature and the easy-to-read meters in the default configuration. I'm yet to customise it, but already getting a lot of use out of it.  EDIT: Just switched to the ART runtime on my Note 3 running Android 4.4.4 and found that the meters in RacingMeter do not render to screen properly (but all logging and so forth works fine). If you switch back to Dalvik, they render properly. Torque Pro's meters outside of the plugin render fine under either runtime. EDIT2: After discussion with the developer, it appears the rendering issue is an incompatibility with ART under CyanogenMod as it works on non-CM setups with ART enabled.
replyContent: Thank you for your report. RacingMeter has been tested on an official version of Android 4.4.4 and the ART runtime with no problems. Maybe ART behaves differently on different devices or custom ROMs, I'll let you know if I have more information. Regards, Fabrice.

replyContent: Hi, This is a plugin that works only in read only, the Bluetooth communication and the OBD2 protocol are managed by Torque, this could be an incorrect behavior of your ECU or Bluetooth adapter. Regards, Fabrice.
